news.title: China: Kaisa Group enters in strategic pact with state-owned firms
news.para: Analysts said Kaisa's move could set an example for other distressed property developers, including China Evergrande Group and Shimao Group, to introduce state-owned enterprises or local governments for their restructuring.

news.title: IndiQube raises $30 million from promoters & WestBridge Capital
news.para: It plans to use the proceeds, to double its PAN India commercial real estate footprint, venture into Tier II cities and to ramp up technology integration.

news.title: Government constrained to revise property tax: Tamil Nadu CM
news.para: ​​Justifying the government decision, Stalin said, "nearly 83 percent of the households in urban Tamil Nadu will not be affected by the present revision."

news.title: Greater Noida authority hikes minimum residential, farmland purchase price
news.para: The GNIDA also announced an increase of around Rs 5,000 to Rs 7,000 per square metre in rates for residential sectors of Greater Noida. The prices of industrial and commercial land have also been hiked but the new rates would be notified soon, it said.

news.title: Greater Noida: Lack of basic civic amenities leaves Surajpur in a lurch
news.para: While the Greater Noida Authority has approved Rs 50 crore to redevelop the town by 2025, residents say the existing woes of sewage dumped all around needed to be dealt with immediately.

news.title: NCLT initiates insolvency process against Ananda Divine Developers
news.para: The insolvency tribunal has appointed Harish Taneja as the Interim Resolution Professional to take over the management of the company while suspending the board of Ananda Divine Developers.

news.title: Greater Noida: GNIDA approves Rs 2,000 crore for land acquisition in 2022-23
news.para: "The Board of GNIDA has approved the budget of Rs 5,104 crore for the financial year 2022-23. It has been approved in the board meeting held under the chairmanship of Industrial Development Commissioner and Noida-Greater Noida Authority Chairman Sanjeev Mittal," an official statement read.

news.title: Motilal Oswal Home Finance receives $50 million commitment from U.S DFC
news.para: This funding commitment is for a period of 15 years and comes at a fixed competitive rate. MOHFL has received the first tranche of this funding from DFC.

news.title: Indore: Buyers demand possession of plots during public hearing
news.para: “We are preparing a seniority list of members and the election of the society would be held soon. There are some other issues we are working on,” cooperative department deputy registrar Madan Gajbhiye said.

news.title: Visakhapatnam development body's auction may set new standard in plot prices
news.para: The VMRDA’s land auctions generally draw a huge number of applications due to the litigation-free nature of its lands.

news.title: Gujarat: 43% increase in stamp duty collection, 25% in sale deeds
news.para: Stamp duty revenue for 2018-19, 2019-20 and 2020-21 was Rs 7,781 crore, Rs 7,701 crore and Rs 7,390 crore, respectively. Compared to 2020-21, stamp duty in 2021-22 increased by more than Rs 3,000 crore.

news.title: Property tax hike for five zones released in Chennai
news.para: An Adyar resident living in a house ranging between 1,201 sq ft and 1,800 sq ft and paying half yearly property tax of Rs 1461 will now have to pay a maximum of Rs 2,922.

news.title: About 200 real estate projects stuck due to delay in approvals: Credai Indore
news.para: The real estate market has seen a rapid recovery post Covid-19 restrictions led by a significant jump in demand for plots and ready-to-move in properties by home buyers but the delay in mandatory permissions has blocked funds and stalled sales of units, claimed developers.

news.title: Ramky Group failed to pay, lied about land in township plan: HMDA to Telangana HC
news.para: Nearly 14 years after initiating the Discovery City project in Srinagar village, the HMDA had issued a termination notice to Ramky in August last year for not fulfilling its obligations as per the joint agreement to develop the township.

news.title: Maharashtra revenue minister to meet IGR on 10,500 illegal registration
news.para: "I will discuss with the IGR regarding these documents and what needs to be done," he said. Thorat added that he would direct officials to check the mutation entries of the documents carried out by the revenue department representatives from the collectorate.
